messages.content: Spider knows SQL
How many heads of the departments are older than 56 from table name head?
SELECT count(*) FROM head WHERE age > 56
Spider knows SQL
List the name, born state and age of the heads of departments ordered by age from table name head.
SELECT name , born_state , age FROM head ORDER BY age
Spider knows SQL
List the creation year, name and budget_in_billions of each department from table name department.
SELECT creation , name , budget_in_billions FROM department
Spider knows SQL
What are the maximum and minimum budget_in_billions of the departments from table name department?
SELECT max(budget_in_billions) , min(budget_in_billions) FROM department
Spider knows SQL
What is the average number of employees of the departments whose rank is between 10 and 15 from table name department?
SELECT avg(num_employees) FROM department WHERE ranking BETWEEN 10 AND 15
Spider knows SQL
What are the names of the heads who are born outside the California state from table name head?
SELECT name FROM head WHERE born_state != 'California'
Spider knows SQL
What are the distinct creation years of the departments managed by a secretary born in state 'Alabama' using table name department and table name management?
SELECT DISTINCT T1.creation FROM department AS T1 JOIN management AS T2 ON T1.department_id = T2.department_id JOIN head AS T3 ON T2.head_id = T3.head_id WHERE T3.born_state = 'Alabama'
Spider knows SQL
What are the names of the states where at least 3 heads were born from table name head?
SELECT born_state FROM head GROUP BY born_state HAVING count(*)  >=  3
Spider knows SQL
In which year were most departments established from table name department?
SELECT creation FROM department GROUP BY creation ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
Spider knows SQL
Show the name and number of employees for the departments managed by heads whose temporary acting value is 'Yes' using table name department and table name management?
SELECT T1.name , T1.num_employees FROM department AS T1 JOIN management AS T2 ON T1.department_id = T2.department_id WHERE T2.temporary_acting = 'Yes'
Spider knows SQL
How many acting statuses are there from table name management?
SELECT count(DISTINCT temporary_acting) FROM management
Spider knows SQL
How many departments are led by heads who are not using table name department and table name management?
SELECT count(*) FROM department WHERE department_id NOT IN (SELECT department_id FROM management);
Spider knows SQL
What are the distinct ages of the heads who are acting using table name department and table name management?
SELECT DISTINCT T1.age FROM management AS T2 JOIN head AS T1 ON T1.head_id = T2.head_id WHERE T2.temporary_acting = 'Yes'
Spider knows SQL
List the states where both the secretary of 'Treasury' head and the secretary of 'Homeland Security' were born using table name department and table name management.

SELECT T3.born_state FROM department AS T1 JOIN management AS T2 ON T1.department_id = T2.department_id JOIN head AS T3 ON T2.head_id = T3.head_id WHERE T1.name = 'Treasury' INTERSECT SELECT T3.born_state FROM department AS T1 JOIN management AS T2 ON T1.department_id = T2.department_id JOIN head AS T3 ON T2.head_id = T3.head_id WHERE T1.name = 'Homeland Security'
Spider knows SQL
Which department has more than 1 head at a time? List the id, name and the number of heads using table name department and table name management.
SELECT T1.department_id , T1.name , count(*) FROM management AS T2 JOIN department AS T1 ON T1.department_id = T2.department_id GROUP BY T1.department_id HAVING count(*) > 1
Spider knows SQL
Which head's name has the substring 'Ha'? List the id and name from table name head.
SELECT head_id , name FROM head WHERE name LIKE '%Ha%'
Spider knows SQL
How many farms are there from table name farm?
SELECT count(*) FROM farm

SELECT avg(Working_Horses) FROM farm WHERE Total_Horses > 5000

Give the average number of working horses on farms with more than 5000 total horses from table name farm.
SELECT avg(Working_Horses) FROM farm WHERE Total_Horses > 5000

SELECT max(Cows) , min(Cows) FROM farm

SELECT max(Cows) , min(Cows) FROM farm

SELECT count(DISTINCT Status) FROM city

Count the number of different statuses from table name city.
SELECT count(DISTINCT Status) FROM city

List official names of cities in descending order of population from table name city.

Show the years and the official names of the host cities of competitions using table name city and table name farm_competition.
SELECT T2.Year , T1.Official_Name FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID = T2.Host_city_ID
Spider knows SQL
Give the years and official names of the cities of each competition using table name city and table name farm_competition.
SELECT T2.Year , T1.Official_Name FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID = T2.Host_city_ID
Spider knows SQL
Show the official names of the cities that have hosted more than one competition using table name city and table name farm_competition.
SELECT T1.Official_Name FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID = T2.Host_city_ID GROUP BY T2.Host_city_ID HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
Spider knows SQL
What are the official names of cities that have hosted more than one competition using table name city and table name farm_competition?
SELECT T1.Official_Name FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID = T2.Host_city_ID GROUP BY T2.Host_city_ID HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
Spider knows SQL
Show the status of the city that has hosted the greatest number of competitions using table name city and table name farm_competition.
SELECT T1.Status FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID = T2.Host_city_ID GROUP BY T2.Host_city_ID ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1
Spider knows SQL
What is the status of the city that has hosted the most competitions using table name city and table name farm_competition?
SELECT T1.Status FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID = T2.Host_city_ID GROUP BY T2.Host_city_ID ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1
Spider knows SQL
Please show the themes of competitions with host cities having populations larger than 1000 using table name city and table name farm_competition.
SELECT T2.Theme FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID = T2.Host_city_ID WHERE T1.Population > 1000
Spider knows SQL
What are the themes of competitions that have corresponding host cities with more than 1000 residents using table name city and table name farm_competition?
SELECT T2.Theme FROM city AS T1 JOIN farm_competition AS T2 ON T1.City_ID = T2.Host_city_ID WHERE T1.Population > 1000
Spider knows SQL
Please show the different statuses of cities and the average population of cities with each status from table name city.
SELECT Status , avg(Population) FROM city GROUP BY Status
Spider knows SQL
What are the statuses and average populations of each city from table name city?
SELECT Status , avg(Population) FROM city GROUP BY Status
Spider knows SQL
Please show the different statuses, ordered in ascending order by the number of cities from table name city.
SELECT Status FROM city GROUP BY Status ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC
Spider knows SQL
Return the different statuses of cities, ascending by frequency from table name city.
SELECT Status FROM city GROUP BY Status ORDER BY COUNT(*) ASC
Spider knows SQL
List the most common type of Status across cities from table name city.
SELECT Status FROM city GROUP BY Status ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1
Spider knows SQL
What is the most common status across all cities from table name city?
SELECT Status FROM city GROUP BY Status ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

List the official names of cities that have not held any competition using table name city and table name farm_competition.
SELECT Official_Name FROM city WHERE City_ID NOT IN (SELECT Host_city_ID FROM farm_competition)
Spider knows SQL
What are the official names of cities that have not hosted a farm competition using table name city and table name farm_competition?
SELECT Official_Name FROM city WHERE City_ID NOT IN (SELECT Host_city_ID FROM farm_competition)
Spider knows SQL
Show the status shared by cities with population bigger than 1500 and smaller than 500 from table name city.
SELECT Status FROM city WHERE Population > 1500 INTERSECT SELECT Status FROM city WHERE Population < 500
Spider knows SQL
Which statuses correspond to both cities that have a population over 1500 and cities that have a population lower than 500 from table name city?
SELECT Status FROM city WHERE Population > 1500 INTERSECT SELECT Status FROM city WHERE Population <500
Spider knows SQL
Find the official names of cities with population bigger than 1500 or smaller than 500 from table name city.
SELECT Official_Name FROM city WHERE Population > 1500 OR Population < 500

What are the official names of cities that have population over 1500 or less than 500 from table name city?
SELECT Official_Name FROM city WHERE Population > 1500 OR Population < 500

SELECT Census_Ranking FROM city WHERE Status != "Village"

SELECT Census_Ranking FROM city WHERE Status != "Village"

which course has most number of registered students using table name courses and table name student_course_registrations?
SELECT T1.course_name FROM courses AS T1 JOIN student_course_registrations AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_Id GROUP BY T1.course_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
Spider knows SQL
What is the name of the course with the most registered students using table name courses and table name student_course_registrations?
SELECT T1.course_name FROM courses AS T1 JOIN student_course_registrations AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_Id GROUP BY T1.course_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
Spider knows SQL
what is id of students who registered some courses but the least number of courses in these students from table name student_course_registrations?
SELECT student_id FROM student_course_registrations GROUP BY student_id ORDER BY count(*) LIMIT 1

What are the ids of the students who registered for some courses but had the least number of courses for all students from table name student_course_registrations?

what are the first name and last name of all candidates using table name candidates and table name people?
SELECT T2.first_name , T2.last_name FROM candidates AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.candidate_id = T2.person_id
Spider knows SQL
What are the first and last names of all the candidates using table name candidates and table name people?
SELECT T2.first_name , T2.last_name FROM candidates AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.candidate_id = T2.person_id

List the id of students who never attends courses from table name student_course_attendance?
SELECT student_id FROM students WHERE student_id NOT IN (SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance)
Spider knows SQL
What are the  ids of every student who has never attended a course from table name student_course_attendance?
SELECT student_id FROM students WHERE student_id NOT IN (SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance)

List the id of students who attended some courses from table name student_course_attendance?
SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance

SELECT student_id FROM student_course_attendance

What are the ids of all students for courses and what are the names of those courses using table name student_course_registrations and table name courses?
SELECT T1.student_id , T2.course_name FROM student_course_registrations AS T1 JOIN courses AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_id
Spider knows SQL
What is detail of the student who most recently registered course using table name student_course_registrations and table name students?
SELECT T2.student_details FROM student_course_registrations AS T1 JOIN students AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id ORDER BY T1.registration_date DESC LIMIT 1

What details do we have on the students who registered for courses most recently using table name student_course_registrations and table name students?

How many students attend course English using table name courses and table name student_course_attendance?
SELECT count(*) FROM courses AS T1 JOIN student_course_attendance AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_id WHERE T1.course_name = "English"
Spider knows SQL
How many students are attending English courses using table name courses and table name student_course_attendance?
SELECT count(*) FROM courses AS T1 JOIN student_course_attendance AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_id WHERE T1.course_name = "English"

How many courses do the student whose id is 171 attend using table name courses and table name student_course_attendance?

How many courses does the student with id 171 actually attend using table name courses and table name student_course_attendance?

What is the name of the student who has attended the most courses using table name student_course_attendance and table name students?
SELECT T2.student_name FROM student_course_attendance AS T1 JOIN students AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

Find id of the candidate whose email is stanley.monahan@example.org?
SELECT T2.candidate_id FROM people AS T1 JOIN candidates AS T2 ON T1.person_id = T2.candidate_id WHERE T1.email_address = "stanley.monahan@example.org"
Spider knows SQL
What is the id of the candidate whose email is stanley.monahan@example.org using table name people and table name candidates?
SELECT T2.candidate_id FROM people AS T1 JOIN candidates AS T2 ON T1.person_id = T2.candidate_id WHERE T1.email_address = "stanley.monahan@example.org"
Spider knows SQL
Find id of the candidate who most recently accessed the course from table name candidate_assessments?
SELECT candidate_id FROM candidate_assessments ORDER BY assessment_date DESC LIMIT 1
Spider knows SQL
What is the id of the candidate who most recently accessed the course from table name candidate_assessments?

SELECT T1.student_details FROM students AS T1 JOIN student_course_registrations AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1
Spider knows SQL
What are the details of the student who registered for the most number of courses using table name students and table name student_course_registrations?

For every student who is registered for some course, how many courses are they registered for using table name students and table name student_course_registrations?

Spider knows SQL

How many registed students do each course have? List course name and the number of their registered students using table name students and table name student_course_registrations and table name courses?
SELECT T3.course_name , count(*) FROM students AS T1 JOIN student_course_registrations AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id JOIN courses AS T3 ON T2.course_id = T3.course_id GROUP BY T2.course_id
Spider knows SQL
For each course id, how many students are registered and what are the course names using table name students and table name student_course_registrations and table name courses?
SELECT T3.course_name , count(*) FROM students AS T1 JOIN student_course_registrations AS T2 ON T1.student_id = T2.student_id JOIN courses AS T3 ON T2.course_id = T3.course_id GROUP BY T2.course_id
Spider knows SQL

Spider knows SQL
What are the ids of the candidates that have an outcome code of Pass from table name candidate_assessments?

Find the cell mobile number of the candidates whose assessment code is "Fail" using table name candidates and table name candidate_assessments and table name people?

SELECT T3.cell_mobile_number FROM candidates AS T1 JOIN candidate_assessments AS T2 ON T1.candidate_id = T2.candidate_id JOIN people AS T3 ON T1.candidate_id = T3.person_id WHERE T2.asessment_outcome_code = "Fail"
Spider knows SQL
What are the cell phone numbers of the candidates that received an assessment code of "Fail" using table name candidates and table name candidate_assessments and table name people?

SELECT T3.cell_mobile_number FROM candidates AS T1 JOIN candidate_assessments AS T2 ON T1.candidate_id = T2.candidate_id JOIN people AS T3 ON T1.candidate_id = T3.person_id WHERE T2.asessment_outcome_code = "Fail"

What are the different cities where students live using table name addresses and table name people_addresses and table name students?
